summary: Starts a new TMUX session, kills the previously running session with the name "qq_red_packet", and then loads the red_packet.yaml configuration file to set up the session environment.

details.comment: Starts a new TMUX session, kills the previously running session with the name "qq_red_packet", and then loads the red_packet.yaml configuration file to set up the session environment.
details.content:
tmux kill-session -t qq_red_packet
tmuxp load red_packet.yaml
